t&dpr=0.2&w=1400 267w,\nhttps://www.datocms-assets.com/28067/1589379442-appideas.png?auto=format&dpr=0.39&w=1400 534w,\nhttps://www.datocms-assets.com/28067/1589379442-appideas.png?auto=format&dpr=0.58&w=1400 801w,\nhttps://www.datocms-assets.com/28067/1589379442-appideas.png?auto=format&dpr=0.77&w=1400 1067w,\nhttps://www.datocms-assets.com/28067/1589379442-appideas.png?auto=format&dpr=1&w=1400 1400w","sizes":"(max-width: 533.6721728081321px) 100vw, 533.6721728081321px"}},"meta":{"firstPublishedAt":"13-05-2020"},"tags":[{"id":"DatoCmsTag-5646091-en","tagName":"programming"}],"articleContent":[{"__typename":"DatoCmsHeading","id":"DatoCmsHeading-4701491-en","headingContent":"1. Countdown Timer"},{"__typename":"DatoCmsParagraph","id":"DatoCmsParagraph-4701492-en","paragraphContent":"Tier: 1-Beginner\nWe all have important events we look forward to in life, birthdays, anniversaries, and holidays to name a few. Wouldn’t it be nice to have an app that counts down the months, days, hours, minutes, and seconds to an event? Countdown Timer is just that app!\nThe objective of Countdown Timer is to provide a continuously decrementing display of the he months, days, hours, minutes, and seconds to a user entered event."},{"__typename":"DatoCmsHeading","id":"DatoCmsHeading-4701493-en","headingContent":"2. FlipImage"},{"__typename":"DatoCmsParagraph","id":"DatoCmsParagraph-4701494-en","paragraphContent":"Tier: 1-Beginner\nIt’s important for Web Developers to understand the basics of manipulating images since rich web applications rely on images to add value to the user interface and user experience (UI/UX).\nFlipImage explores one aspect of image manipulation — image rotation. This app displays a square pane containing a single image presented in a 2x2 matrix. Using a set of up, down, left, and right arrows adjacent to each of the images the user may flip them vertically or horizontally.\nYou must only use native HTML, CSS, and Javascript to implement this app. Image packages and libraries are not allowed."}]},"allDatoCmsArticle":{"edges":[{"node":{"id":"DatoCmsArticle-5645977-en","title":"Things nobody ever taught me about CSS"}},{"node":{"id":"DatoCmsArticle-5645476-en","title":"The 4px baseline grid - the present"}},{"node":{"id":"DatoCmsArticle-5645505-en","title":"Recoil.js — The New, Better State Management Library for React"}},{"node":{"id":"DatoCmsArticle-4700456-en","title":"Goodbye, Object Oriented Programming"}},{"node":{"id":"DatoCmsArticle-5645416-en","title":"7 Alternatives to the <div> HTML Tag"}},{"node":{"id":"DatoCmsArticle-4704245-en","title":"The perfect trip Norway"}},{"node":{"id":"DatoCmsArticle-5645986-en","title":"What Are Articles?"}},{"node":{"id":"DatoCmsArticle-4701495-en","title":"15 App Ideas to Build and Level Up your Coding Skills"}}]}},"pageContext":{"id":"DatoCmsArticle-4701495-en"}}}